### Describe the bug

Body parameters are incorrectly emitted as "parameters" by Swagger (in addition to `requestBody`) when using the `WithOpenApi()` extension method from `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi`. The parameter has no schema (just a name) in the swagger document. For example, the following endpoint: 

```csharp
app.MapPost("/fruit/{id}", (string id, Fruit fruit) => fruit)
    .WithOpenApi();
```

Produces a swagger.json similar to:

```json
"paths": {
    "/fruit/{id}": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "fruit"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "id",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {                     // Should not exist
            "name": "fruit",    //
            "required": true    //
          }                     //
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Fruit"
              }
            }
          },
          "required": true
        },
    }
}
```

This leads to incorrect handling in Swagger UI (for example)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18755388/189841987-4aa0ead2-01b0-4a9a-88ee-7ec42f561fa3.png)


### Expected Behavior

The body endpoint parameter should not appear as a parameter in the swagger schema. This is the behaviour if you _don't_ call `WithOpenApi()`: 

```json
"paths": {
    "/fruit/{id}": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "fruit"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "id",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Fruit"
              }
            }
          },
          "required": true
        },
    }
}
```

### Steps To Reproduce

A new minimal API project, using .NET 7 preview 7, and the following packages:

```xml
  <ItemGroup>	
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi" Version="7.0.0-preview.7.22376.6" />
    <PackageReference Include="swashbuckle.aspnetcore" Version="6.4.0" />
  </ItemGroup>
```

Program.cs:

```csharp
WebApplicationBuilder builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

builder.Services.AddEndpointsApiExplorer();
builder.Services.AddSwaggerGen();

WebApplication app = builder.Build();

app.UseSwagger();
app.UseSwaggerUI();

app.MapPost("/fruit/{id}",(string id, Fruit fruit) => fruit)
    .WithOpenApi();

app.Run();

record Fruit(string Name, int Stock);
```

